    "author": "1874427056618168320",
    "displayName": "1874427056618168320",
    "text": "Suppression of free speech...\nWhat has become an ingrained attitude of \"the left\" is an intolerance of other political opinions. They reserve to themselves the right to decide who can, and who cannot speak. \nNow this attitude is not applied to men in black boots goose-stepping around the place, but an ever-widening expanse of politics \"they don't like\". Not liking something now equates to \"it must be banned\".\nThis is an inherent intolerance and totalitarian attitude.\nYou merely have to ask the question: If these people were in government, how would they treat their political opponents?\nYou can find the historical answer in Communist Russia, after 1918, Communist China and North Korea. Political opponents are locked up, shot, put in gulags and face the firing squad.  You can even see the beginnings of this mentality in the crowd's attitude in this video.",
